3076fdcf-e345-4e11-a210-456b9de125e0.0771cfbe-a0a0-46da-a24a-165df2e91455.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

3076fdcf-e345-4e11-a210-456b9de125e0.3f48d7aa-f5c8-49f9-aae5-e112918f6a52.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal

3076fdcf-e345-4e11-a210-456b9de125e0.5a3e650a-ede4-41dd-a3ca-557b18674fa3.description=
Runs a SQL query against an Oracle database, using the information in the tnsnames.ora file.  
The first row is returned on the first run of the operation. Subsequent calls with the same information return the other rows.

Inputs\:
    TNSPath -The path to the folder of the TNS file tnsnames.ora. This path must be accessible by the OO RAS service. For example, if the RAS and the Oracle server are installed on the same Windows system, the TNSPath might look like “C\:\app\Administrator\product\11.1.0\db_1\network\admin”. If the RAS and the Oracle server are on different Windows systems, you can copy the tnsnames.ora file  to the RAS system. The TNSPath might look like “C\:\Program Files\Hewlett-Packard\Operations Orchestration\RAS\Java\Default\webapp\conf” or “C\:\Temp” depending on where you place the .ora file. 
    TNSEntry - The entry name in the tnsnames.ora file that contains the connection information. For example, the value for the TNSEntry input is “TestEntry” if the content in the tnsnames.ora file looks like the following\: 

TestEntry \=
  (DESCRIPTION \=
   (ADDRESS \= (PROTOCOL \= TCP)(HOST \= 16.110.111.111)(PORT \= 1521))
   (CONNECT_DATA \=
     (SERVER \= DEDICATED)
     (SERVICE_NAME \= orcl)
   )
 )

    Username - The username to connect to the Oracle database. 
    Password - The password for the Username.
    Command - The command to execute. 
    Delimiter – The delimiter to use between the columns in the returnResult result.
    Key – The key to use to keep multiple query results distinct.
    timeout - Seconds to wait before timing out the SQL command execution.
Default values\: 0 

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. Returned the data returned for each row separated by the value you specified in the Delimiter input (for example, “key16|lst|16”).
    columnNames - The names of the columns returned, separated by the value you specified in the Delimiter input (for example, “MYKEY|NAME|ID”).
    rowsLeft - The number of rows remaining that match the query. 

Responses\:
    more items - More rows are available for retrieval.
    no more items - No more rows are available.
    failure - There was an error executing the command.

Notes\:
1. This operation only supports Oracle. 
2. This operation can only execute the "SELECT" statement. For statements that modify the database, use the TNS Names SQL Command operation.

flow.name: DB_GetResourcePool

scriptlet.name: default
default

staticBinding.value:
SELECT RESPOOLID, MAXDISK,HPIO, VMMP_IP FROM ( SELECT UNIQUE(M.RESPOOLID),M.MAXDISK,CC.HPIO,VMMP.IP AS VMMP_IP, M.MAXSYS - M.ALLOCSYS AS FREESYS FROM RVW_MOERESPOOLALLOC M INNER JOIN CLOUDCELL CC ON M.CCNAME = CC.CCNAME INNER JOIN DATACENTER DC ON CC.DCNAME = DC.DCNAME LEFT JOIN RESPOOL_VMMP RES_VM ON M.RESPOOLID = RES_VM.RESPOOLID LEFT JOIN VMMP VMMP ON CC.CCNAME = VMMP.CCNAME AND RES_VM.VMMP_TYPE = VMMP.VMMP_TYPE WHERE CC.CATNAME = '${db.getresourcepool.catname}' ${db.getresourcepool.ccname.query} ${db.getresourcepool.dcacronym.query} AND M.SLALEVEL = '${db.getresourcepool.slalevel}' AND M.SYSTEMTYPE = '${db.getresourcepool.systemtype}' AND M.MAXSYS - M.ALLOCSYS > 0 AND M.PURPOSE = '${db.getresourcepool.purpose}' AND VMMP.VMMP_TYPE ='${db.getresourcepool.vmmp.type}' AND M.RESPOOLID LIKE '%${server.1.cpu}%${server.1.mem}%' UNION
SELECT UNIQUE(M.RESPOOLID),M.MAXDISK,CC.HPIO, NULL AS VMMP_IP, M.MAXSYS - M.ALLOCSYS AS FREESYS FROM RVW_MOERESPOOLALLOC M INNER JOIN CLOUDCELL CC ON M.CCNAME = CC.CCNAME INNER JOIN DATACENTER DC ON CC.DCNAME = DC.DCNAME INNER JOIN TSHIRTSIZES SZ ON M.SYSTEMTYPE = (SZ.HARDWARE || SZ.TSIZE) WHERE CC.CATNAME = '${db.getresourcepool.catname}' ${db.getresourcepool.ccname.query} ${db.getresourcepool.dcacronym.query} AND M.SLALEVEL = '${db.getresourcepool.slalevel}' AND M.SYSTEMTYPE = '${db.getresourcepool.systemtype}' AND M.MAXSYS - M.ALLOCSYS > 0 AND M.PURPOSE = '${db.getresourcepool.purpose}' AND M.RESPOOLID LIKE '%${server.1.cpu}%${server.1.mem}%' )
ORDER BY FREESYS DESC

scriptlet.name: default

staticBinding.value: SELECT V.VMTPLLOC,V.VMTPLGUID, V.VMTPLNAME FROM VMTEMPLATES V WHERE V.RESPOOLID = '${db.getresourcepool.resourcepool}' AND V.OS = '${db.getresourcepool.os}' AND V.ISCLIENTSUPPLIED='${server.1.isclientsupplied}' AND V.VMTPLNAME='${server.1.templatename}'

SELECT a.VMTPLNAME FROM VMTEMPLATES a, MOERESPOOL b WHERE a.RESPOOLID=b.RESPOOLID AND a.OS='${db.getresourcepool.os}' AND a.ISCLIENTSUPPLIED='${server.1.isclientsupplied}' AND b.CCNAME='${db.getresourcepool.ccname}' AND b.SLALEVEL='SLA1' AND b.SYSTEMTYPE='V' AND a.VMTPLNAME = '${server.1.templatename}'
SELECT V.VMTPLLOC,V.VMTPLGUID, V.VMTPLNAME FROM VMTEMPLATES V WHERE V.RESPOOLID = '${db.getresourcepool.resourcepool}' AND V.OS = '${db.getresourcepool.os}' AND ISCLIENTSUPPLIED is NULL

SELECT UNIQUE(M.RESPOOLID),M.MAXDISK,CC.HPIO, NULL AS VMMP_IP, M.MAXSYS - M.ALLOCSYS AS FREESYS FROM RVW_MOERESPOOLALLOC M INNER JOIN CLOUDCELL CC ON M.CCNAME = CC.CCNAME INNER JOIN DATACENTER DC ON CC.DCNAME = DC.DCNAME INNER JOIN TSHIRTSIZES SZ ON M.SYSTEMTYPE = (SZ.HARDWARE || SZ.TSIZE) WHERE CC.CATNAME = '${db.getresourcepool.catname}' ${db.getresourcepool.ccname.query} ${db.getresourcepool.dcacronym.query} AND M.SLALEVEL = '${db.getresourcepool.slalevel}' AND M.SYSTEMTYPE = '${db.getresourcepool.systemtype}' AND M.MAXSYS - M.ALLOCSYS > 0 AND M.PURPOSE = '${db.getresourcepool.purpose}' )
ORDER BY FREESYS DESC
